hed over Alice's desire to be something more than "an ornament to society"—a wish eventually granted as Frank's long absences and chronic ill health required Allie to take responsibility for herself and their daughter. With insights into military campaigns on the Great Plains in the years 1865–1890 and a revealing look at the human side of those campaigns, A Long March will appeal to a wide audience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezWest (U.S.). 0aIndians of North AmericaxWarsy1866-1895. 0aOfficers' spouseszWest (U.S.)vBiography. 0aSoldierszWest (U.S.)vBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Military.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292761773423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292761773/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK